Former Senate President, Dr Abubakar Bukola Saraki, has reacted to the passing of the traditional ruler of Oyo kingdom, Oba Lamidi Adeyemi who died at the weekend after 52 years on the throne. In a condolence message, Dr Saraki said the late monarch lived a full and exemplary life dedicated to serving the people. “After almost 52-years on the throne, our Royal Father, Oba Lamidi Adeyemi, the Alaafin of Oyo, has joined his ancestors. “As we mourn the passing of His Royal Highness, we celebrate the fact that he lived a full and exemplary life that was dedicated to serving people,” he stated. The former two-term governor of Kwara State prayed that the Almighty God grants the government and people of Oyo State strength to bear the loss.